<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-6E646550-91AF-404C-A660-198768D9838C" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-6E646550-91AF-404C-A660-198768D9838C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">License mechanism</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-01A48207-B51C-4A1B-8EB4-25FA5067528D"><p class="- topic/p "> Licenses are managed in the back-office. Initially licenses are created in ILMS with a Product license number and no relation to a specific serial number. Below the components and order visualized: 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-35825C34-4EBF-472E-91E0-77D8BB5E8D56"><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-9337F13A-B376-4D86-A00E-DF73B78A000A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-9337F13A-B376-4D86-A00E-DF73B78A000A-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">On the engine the product license needs to be inserted on the settings editor. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The next step is that the product license together hardware identifiers including the serial number are transferred (as a summary file) to the back-office. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The back-office interprets the summary file and returns actual licenses to the engine. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As a last step the licenses must be loaded and the machine needs to effectuate the license by a restart. 
</p><table class="- topic/table " id="GUID-64D3D262-07D1-4247-A5CB-AC741A175502"><tgroup class="- topic/tgroup " cols="4"><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*"/><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*"/><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*"/><colspec class="- topic/colspec " colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*"/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Transfer mechanism 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> Duration 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> notes 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">procedures 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">On Remote Service (ORS) 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">10 minutes 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Requires ORS connection. 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="AutoLicenseViaORS" href="GUID-66521B0A-9EE4-432D-8C42-473926C9FB43.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to request a license via ORS?>How to request a license via ORS</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Followed by installation of the license: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="GEN_INST_LICENSE_ORS_001" href="GUID-4D9B803A-BA12-4035-80B2-CFBB77288B40.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Install a license via ORS?>Install a license via ORS</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Web portal 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> 20 minutes 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Requires additionally the order number that was used to create the license. 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="License_web" href="GUID-10EC12F3-C3B8-4390-8FCB-83A4192C872F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to request a license via the web?>How to request a license via the web</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Followed by installation of the license: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="GENINSTLICENCE002" href="GUID-A5731826-4ADE-4A39-807A-9F6B14629783.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Install a license received via e-mail?>Install a license received via e-mail</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col1" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p ">Email to 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">local/regional 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">back-office engineer 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col2" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> 30 minutes 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col3" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "> Heavily dependent on the availability of the back-office engineer. 
</p></entry><entry class="- topic/entry " colname="col4" valign="top"><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="GEN_INST_LICENSE_EMAIL" href="GUID-1B6B5918-BE50-4455-8B0C-BF62C907AF58.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to request a license via e-mail?>How to request a license via e-mail</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Followed by installation of the license: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref class="- topic/xref " keyref="GENINSTLICENCE002" href="GUID-A5731826-4ADE-4A39-807A-9F6B14629783.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Install a license received via e-mail?>Install a license received via e-mail</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-762C2499-734B-4498-9203-AAC05299A9A9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Adding /removing a license</title><p class="- topic/p ">An additional license needs to be added in the back-office first. When this is done the configured licenses need to be transferred to the product again. 
</p><table id="GUID-44EC20F7-323B-444F-844D-2E95C9165616" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Transfer mechanism 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Duration 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> notes 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">procedures 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">On Remote Service (ORS) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 minutes 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> When the license is updated the license is automatically transferred to the engine . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The new license only needs to be applied by the customer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="GEN_INST_UPDATE_LICENSE_ORS" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B240EAE5-F36D-4762-8DCF-692A8F3BCB4A.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Element ID :GUID-B240EAE5-F36D-4762-8DCF-692A8F3BCB4A?>How to update a license via ORS</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Web portal 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 20 minutes 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Tech needs to be onsite and additionally requires the order number that was used to create the license. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The complete cycle from request to installation needs to be executed. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="License_web" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-10EC12F3-C3B8-4390-8FCB-83A4192C872F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to request a license via the web?>How to request a license via the web</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Followed by installation of the license: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="GENINSTLICENCE002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A5731826-4ADE-4A39-807A-9F6B14629783.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Install a license received via e-mail?>Install a license received via e-mail</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Email to 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">local/regional 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">back-office engineer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 30 minutes 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The back-office engineer can generate the license files an send those to the technician that needs to install the licenses on the machine. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Dependency on the availability of the back-office engineer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> On reception of the license: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="GENINSTLICENCE002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-A5731826-4ADE-4A39-807A-9F6B14629783.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Install a license received via e-mail?>Install a license received via e-mail</xref> 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-E034FCF0-35BA-494E-B7D4-E2FFEC2B2F79" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Expiry</title><p class="- topic/p "> When temporary licenses almost expire, the user is informed on the engine UI that the license will expire. The expiration will always expire at the end of a job. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-26A6FDA9-D4D7-445B-91AA-D9608E775DBB.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>